  "texts": [
    "Intuitively, each window is associated with all the sensor states whose interval intersects with the window interval.",
    "More formally, a window 𝑤 𝑡 over the interval [𝑡, 𝑡 + 𝜏] is associated with the sensor states 𝑠𝑡 (𝜎, 𝑡 𝑠, 𝑡 𝑒) such that 𝑡 𝑠 ≤ 𝑡 + 𝜏 and 𝑡 𝑒 ≥ 𝑡.Note that a window may be associated with multiple states even derived from different sensors.",
    "Based on the time intervals, we distinguish three categories that will be useful for text generation:• Inner states: this is the case of 𝑡 𝑠 ≥ 𝑡 and 𝑡 𝑒 ≤ 𝑡 + 𝜏.",
    "This represents the simple case of the state occurring completely within the window.",
    "• Already active states: this is the case of 𝑡 𝑠 < 𝑡."
  ],
